Place all ingredients, except fresh sage leaves, into blender. Blend until smooth. Press mixture through fine sieve, into an 8 inch square baking dish (discard solids). Cover and freeze, stirring and crushing lumps with fork ever 1/2 hour, for a total of three hours. Stirring procedure is very important, to prevent mixture from freezing into a solid frozen lump. Texture should be ice crystals. Serve immediately in chilled wine glasses, garnish with fresh sage leaves.